modules.description: Provides functions to parse and manipulate diff files in both loosely specified and git formats, including handling file renames and separating diff blocks. Works with strings representing diff content and extracts structured information like file paths and change details. Used to validate signed updates in package managers by ensuring correct application of line-based differences.

Parses and applies unified diffs, handling operations like adding, deleting, and modifying lines in text. Works with hunk structures, operation types, and diff records to represent and manipulate changes. Used to generate or apply patches to file content, such as integrating code changes or resolving conflicts.
